{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This is my first post on my new fake blog! How exciting!"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I'm sure I'll write a lot more interesting things in the future."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Oh, and here's a great quote from this Wikipedia on\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salted_duck_egg"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"salted duck eggs"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"blockquote","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A salted duck egg is a Chinese preserved food product made by soaking duck\neggs in brine, or packing each egg in damp, salted charcoal. In Asian\nsupermarkets, these eggs are sometimes sold covered in a thick layer of salted\ncharcoal paste. The eggs may also be sold with the salted paste removed,\nwrapped in plastic, and vacuum packed. From the salt curing process, the\nsalted duck eggs have a briny aroma, a gelatin-like egg white and a\nfirm-textured, round yolk that is bright orange-red in color."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"div","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"rehype-image","properties":{"src":"./salty_egg.jpg","rehyped":"{\"base64\":\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\",\"aspectRatio\":1.3333333333333333,\"src\":\"/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/d0587/salty_egg.jpg\",\"srcSet\":\"/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/e597a/salty_egg.jpg 200w,\\n/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/5a822/salty_egg.jpg 400w,\\n/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/d0587/salty_egg.jpg 800w,\\n/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/f2b88/salty_egg.jpg 1200w,\\n/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/07141/salty_egg.jpg 1600w,\\n/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/b9b6f/salty_egg.jpg 2048w\",\"srcSetType\":\"image/jpeg\",\"sizes\":\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\",\"originalImg\":\"/static/8058f3f26913fea3b6a89a73344fe94a/b9b6f/salty_egg.jpg\",\"originalName\":\"salty_egg.jpg\",\"density\":300,\"presentationWidth\":800,\"presentationHeight\":600}"},"children":[]}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"path":"/why","title":"A Blog?","date":"25.02.2019"}}},"pageContext":{}}